**Bull-Bear Market Cycle Indicator:** The bull/bear market cycle indicator is a momentum metric. It measures the difference between the P&L Index and its 365-day moving average. Bull cycle - indicator above 0. Bear cycle - indicator below 0 and below its 365-day moving average. Most of the returns of bitcoin are made when the indicator is above 0 (bull market cycle). Prices enter into bear mode when the indicators switch from Bull to BEAR.

CPI Update & Crypto Impact The Consumer Price Index (CPI) measures inflation and is released once a month. Its a key factor that can shake up both traditional and crypto markets. Why Does It Matter to Crypto?  Interest Rates: Lower CPI = chance of lower interest rates, good for crypto. Higher CPI = tighter policies, bad for crypto.  Market Moves: Positive CPI can boost crypto prices; negative data can trigger sell-offs.  Dollar Value: A weak dollar (often after low CPI) tends to push Bitcoin and altcoins higher. Stay Alert: CPI news often brings price swings in crypto. Smart traders keep an eye on it monthly.
